title.narrative: PROGRAMME PLANNING, MONITORING & REPORTING ON RESULTS

description.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners are provided guidance, tools and resources to effectively plan and monitor programmes and report on results, which contributes to Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: India Country Programme is effectively and efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children

title.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners are provided guidance, tools and resources to effectively plan and monitor programmes and report onresults

description.narrative: In 2021, the sections and state offices in India Country office were provided support and guidance to drive results driven programming resulting in revision of HAC 2021, submission of quarterly humanitarian reporting, timely and quality submission of donor reports, capacities built on Knowledge management and ECM sites, timely circulation of budget management products and ensuring compliance of HACT obligations. Strategic moment of reflection was facilitated resulting in the development of the Strategic intent for the next CP(2023-27). Continued roll out of RAM-India and eTools enhancement and modules strengthened planning, monitoring and reporting. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
